Former Commissioner for Transportation in Lagos State, and a chieftain of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Chief Lanre Razak has thrown his weight behind the presidential ambition of Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, saying he has what it takes to build on the successes recorded by President Muhammadu Buhari. Razaq while speaking with journalists in Lagos said he is in full support of the initiative of Senator Olamilekan Solomon on, ‘Tinubu 2023 Presidency Project,’ saying, it is a laudable project that will move the country to greater heights after President Muhammadu Buhari’s tenure in 2023. It would be recall that Senator Olamilekan in an interview granted recently stressed the need for the national leader of the APC Asiwaju Tinubu to succeed President Buhari in 2023, saying, Tinubu, who is his mentor and political godfather possessed all the qualities required to make a good President. Razak, also said he has the strong conviction that, the best thing all patriotic Nigerians can do for President Buhari is to bring up a worthy successor like Tinubu, who shares the aspiration of Buhari, to succeed him to ensure continuity of his good work he started in office. “Tinubu is eminently qualified to succeed President Buhari in 2023, no doubt. His political experience, economic acumen, social exposure and being a tested and trusted team leader have put him at vantage position to succeed Buhari. “He is a onetime Senator of the Federal Republic of Nigeria and Governor of the most sophisticated state in Nigeria, Lagos. Thus, for now, he is the best material for the job. And with him as the next President, Nigeria will continue to be in a safe hand as it is now,” Razak said. According to him, Senator Solomon’s call for Tinubu’s presidency in 2023 tallies with ,”My own conviction that the APC National Leader has all what it takes to move the country further forward after President Buhari.” 